This article is a summary of an executive order signed by President Joe Biden to promote diversity, equity, inclusion, and accessibility in the Federal Government. The order establishes that the Federal Government should be a model for diversity and inclusivity, and outlines various policies and initiatives to achieve this goal. It emphasizes the importance of recruiting, hiring, developing, promoting, and retaining a diverse workforce, and removing barriers to equal opportunity. The order also calls for the development of a Government-wide Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Accessibility Strategic Plan, as well as the collection and analysis of demographic data to measure progress. It addresses the advancement of equity for employees with disabilities and LGBTQ+ employees, as well as promoting paid internships and expanding employment opportunities for formerly incarcerated individuals. The order also includes provisions to address pay equity and improve professional development and training programs.